reviews.review_text: 3 Shows in 48 hours The third and final "20th Anniversary" shows, amazing. During the 2nd set, the band took a lot of time to discuss what to play next and the anticipation from the crowd grew to a frenzy that made all the hair on your body stand up. What would it be? Star? Stephen? Someone behind me  said "Brent's on the harpsicord, it's going to be Mountains of the Moon". My heart jumped. And then the first notes from Jerry...CRIPTICAL!!! The place went WILD; I've never heard such a loud roar, like a jet engine. Great stuff, canÂt find that no more. 15 stars for this trio of shows.

I always wondered what the aud. sounded like Nice Job. 

Had this and Hershey Park 85 sbd's on cassete way back when. This is a super nice audience tape. I still will most likely pull out the board when listening to this second set but this aud is great for the Crypt>TOO>Crypt bust out - I never knew how jacked the crowd got till I heard this. This whole 2nd set is definitely the the highlight of this show, classic 85 factor. This aud. easily makes up for the easy access to the old board.

5 star audience recording.
